&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As Community and Brand Manager, you’ll be the guardian and amplifier of the ThriveCart brand while owning the day-to-day health, engagement, and communication within our community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a proactive role - not reactive moderation. You will ensure ThriveCart looks, sounds, and feels unmistakably ThriveCart everywhere it shows up - while consistently providing updates, sharing timelines and key dates, surfacing important product and company news, and ensuring members feel heard, supported, and excited to be part of ThriveCart.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be the voice of the brand inside the community and across key touchpoints - translating internal updates into clear, friendly, and trustworthy communication for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role blends strategy and execution: part brand steward, part community leader.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll work closely with marketing, product, support, content, design, and leadership to ensure alignment, clarity, and consistency across every channel.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Community Engagement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively manage and engage with the ThriveCart community on a daily basis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Foster a welcoming, helpful, and professional environment aligned with ThriveCart’s brand values&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Encourage meaningful discussion, participation, and peer-to-peer support&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Consistently share product updates, roadmap highlights, timelines, and key dates with the community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Translate internal information into clear, customer-friendly posts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure the community is always informed — no silence, no ambiguity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the voice of ThriveCart within the community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicate with clarity, empathy, and confidence, even during sensitive or high-traffic moments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Plan, host, and moderate webinars, tech-ins, and community sessions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate agendas, speakers, and follow-ups to ensure smooth execution&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage attendees during live sessions and drive post-event discussion&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support affiliate communications within the community, sharing updates and acting as liaison when needed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gather feedback, questions, and sentiment from the community&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surface recurring themes, concerns, and opportunities to internal teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advocate for the community while aligning with company goals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Brand Ownership &amp;amp; Governance&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the day-to-day brand guardian for all community-facing content, ensuring every post, reply, announcement, and engagement touchpoint consistently reflects ThriveCart&#39;s voice, tone, and messaging standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply ThriveCart&#39;s brand guidelines when creating and publishing community content across all platforms, including forums, social channels, and member communications — no content goes out that isn&#39;t on-brand.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and provide brand feedback on community-generated campaigns, partner spotlights, and user-submitted content before publication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain a working knowledge of ThriveCart&#39;s brand guidelines and flag inconsistencies or drift when spotted across community channels, escalating where needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support product launches and campaigns by crafting community announcements and engagement content that aligns with the broader campaign messaging and brand positioning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor community sentiment and member feedback to surface insights that inform how ThriveCart&#39;s brand voice is landing — and where it could be clearer,

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About ThriveCart:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;ThriveCart is a high-growth infrastructure ecosystem powering online commerce and digital&amp;nbsp;marketing at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As we expand our footprint upstream, we are launching an elite, nimble outbound sales unit&amp;nbsp;consisting of three (3) US-based Sales Development Representatives. This team will pioneer our&amp;nbsp;push into the mid-market and enterprise ecosystem, targeting high-volume platforms looking&amp;nbsp;for agile, headless-adjacent checkout and marketing stack solutions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remote (US-Based)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview&lt;/strong&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a pure hunting role built for individuals who love the challenge of outbound prospecting&amp;nbsp;and creating opportunities from scratch. You will target platforms in the $5M to $50M revenue&lt;br&gt;tier, initiating conversations around flexible infrastructure and custom checkouts while helping&amp;nbsp;shape our evolving enterprise motion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;High-Volume Outbound Outreach: Execute consistent daily cold-calling and highly targeted&amp;nbsp;email sequences to connect with enterprise decision-makers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Upstream Prospecting: Identify, map, and engage key stakeholder accounts generating $5M–$50M in platform revenue.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Value Proposition: Introduce platforms to our modern commerce solutions, emphasizing&amp;nbsp;customizable, headless-style capabilities designed to solve scaling bottlenecks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Pipeline Creation: Own the top of the funnel, converting cold prospects into qualified discovery&amp;nbsp;meetings for our commercial leadership team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Feedback Loop: Partner directly with executive leadership to share real-time market feedback&amp;nbsp;and help refine our enterprise go-to-market strategy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Skills:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;p-pdf_iframe__page&quot; data-page-number=&quot;1&quot;&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;textLayer&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven Prospector: You bring energy, persistence, and strong communication skills. You enjoy&amp;nbsp;opening doors, building relationships, and creating opportunities where none previously&amp;nbsp;existed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Performance Driven: You are motivated by achievement and excited by a compensation&amp;nbsp;structure that rewards results with uncapped earning potential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI First: You likely already use AI tools to improve productivity and are constantly exploring&amp;nbsp;new ways to increase effectiveness through automation and emerging technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ambiguous &amp;amp; Adaptable: You thrive in entrepreneurial environments where products,&amp;nbsp;messaging, and strategy continue to evolve.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tech-Fluent: You can confidently discuss software, fintech, and payment-related concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;US-Based Resilience: You operate effectively in a remote environment, maintain strong&lt;br&gt;activity levels, and manage your time independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What&#39;s in it for You?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Uncapped Financial Upside: A commission structure designed to reward opportunity creation and pipeline generation with significant earning potential.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strategic Impact: As one of the first three SDRs in this enterprise initiative, your contributions&amp;nbsp;will directly influence our long-term enterprise sales playbook.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The Portfolio Edge: Leverage the market credibility of established software brands that already&amp;nbsp;support significant global transaction volumes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Piktochart:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Piktochart is a web-based graphic design platform that empowers users to create professional-grade visuals, including infographics, presentations, and videos, without the need for extensive design experience. Founded in 2011, Piktochart has grown into a global team of developers, designers, marketers, and support staff dedicated to building the best visual storytelling tool on the internet.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remote - LATAM or Europe&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Lead Backend Engineer is responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining the core backend architecture that powers Piktochart&#39;s platform. This role focuses on building scalable, secure, and high-performing systems while collaborating closely with Product, Design, and Engineering teams to deliver reliable solutions that enhance the user experience and support platform growth.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What Your Work Will Entail:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, develop, and maintain the core backend architecture,&amp;nbsp;ensuring it is scalable, secure, and optimized for performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with front-end developers, product managers, and&amp;nbsp;UX/UI teams to build seamless and integrated backend solutions that&amp;nbsp;align with product requirements and&amp;nbsp;user needs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor and improve the backend system’s reliability, performance,&amp;nbsp;and security, implementing solutions to handle high-volume requests&amp;nbsp;and ensure smooth operation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee database architecture and optimize queries, ensuring data&amp;nbsp;integrity and performance while managing storage and scalability&amp;nbsp;challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct code reviews to ensure high-quality, maintainable, and&amp;nbsp;well-documented code, promoting a culture of excellence in backend&amp;nbsp;development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate and integrate new technologies, frameworks, and tools to&amp;nbsp;enhance the backend infrastructure and improve development&amp;nbsp;efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Bring To This Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of experience in backend software development.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong expertise in Ruby on Rails and TypeScript.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solid understanding of software architecture, backend design patterns, and scalable system design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience building and maintaining APIs, backend services, and database-driven applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of relational databases and performance optimization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of application security and modern development best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with cloud infrastructure and CI/CD workflows.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong problem-solving, communication, and collaboration skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience mentoring developers and contributing to technical leadership initiatives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using AI Agents and implementing and building AI tools and Agents.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Learn More About Piktochart:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our team thrives on collaboration, innovation, and continuous growth. We foster an open environment with regular knowledge-sharing sessions and encourage active participation in shaping the platform. Our values include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Commit to Excellence&lt;/strong&gt; – We believe in delivering high-quality work and continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;User-Focused Problem Solving&lt;/strong&gt; – Every line of code should contribute to solving a real problem for our users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Team Collaboration&lt;/s

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About ThriveCart&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-teams=&quot;true&quot;&gt;ThriveCart is the leading no-code sales platform for digital course creators, coaches, entrepreneurs, and online businesses looking to boost revenue, drive conversions, and scale audiences. ThriveCart powers over 65,000 businesses and 12 million enrolled students, generating over $2 billion in annual sales. The platform provides all the tools businesses need to create high-converting checkout experiences, manage powerful affiliate campaigns, and deliver seamless student experiences with its built-in learning management system, Learn/Learn+.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Remote - UK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Lead Quality Assurance Engineer coordinates QA activities across the team while remaining actively involved in testing and automation. This role drives quality standards, supports release readiness, improves QA processes, and helps ensure the delivery of reliable, high-quality software.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Technical Excellence&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive the continued development and improvement of test automation frameworks and testing processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support and improve automated testing within CI/CD pipelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to improve test coverage, reliability, and overall product quality.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate and recommend testing tools, frameworks, and technologies that enhance QA effectiveness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help establish and maintain testing standards, documentation, and QA best practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Promote effective use of AI tools to improve test automation, test case generation, defect analysis, and overall QA efficiency.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ownership &amp;amp; Delivery&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate QA activities across releases to ensure quality standards are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead test planning, execution, validation, and post-release verification efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor product quality, identify risks, and work with engineering teams to address issues proactively.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support incident investigation, defect triage, and root cause analysis activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help improve testing environments, release readiness processes, and quality monitoring practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Balance delivery timelines with quality expectations and provide recommendations on release readiness.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Team &amp;amp; Company Impact&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and support QA team members while promoting quality best practices across engineering teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Engineering Managers, Product Managers, and developers to foster a culture of shared quality ownership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide input on quality risks, testing strategy, and process improvements during planning and development activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive initiatives that improve QA efficiency, collaboration, and consistency across multiple teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the ongoing evolution of QA standards, automation practices, and team processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
